      "file": "\\\\?\\C:\\tmp\\multi-agent-pipeline\\.deepseek\\state\\subagents.v1.json",
      "line_number": 228,
      "line": "                \"content\": \"<file path=\\\"C:\\\\tmp\\\\multi-agent-pipeline\\\\docs\\\\architecture_v2.md\\\" total_lines=\\\"539\\\" shown_lines=\\\"1-100\\\" truncated=\\\"true\\\" next_start_line=\\\"101\\\">\\n     1│ # multi-agent-pipeline Architecture v2.0\\n     2│ \\n     3│ ## Overview\\n     4│ \\n     5│ This document defines the redesigned architecture for the multi-agent-pipeline system, addressing all identified design flaws and establishing a clean separation of concerns between static configuration, dynamic state, and collaborative tooling.\\n     6│ \\n     7│ ## Core Principles\\n     8│ \\n     9│ 1. **Static vs Dynamic Separation**: features.json defines WHAT to build; DB records WHO is building it and HOW MUCH it costs; GitHub tracks the collaboration artifacts.\\n    10│ 2. **Wave Ordering is Advisory**: Wave assignments in features.json are planning hints, not enforced constraints. The actual execution order is determined by the orchestrator (Hermes) based on dependency analysis, agent availability, and task complexity.\\n    11│ 3. **Agent Communication Resilience**: Primary channel is delegate_task; fallback channels include direct file-based communication and MCP-based messaging.\\n    12│ 4. **Approval Flexibility**: Supports both granular L1/L2/L3 review and blanket user authorization for autonomous execution.\\n    13│ 5. **Tool Self-Hosting**: The pipeline manages its own development using itself.\\n    14│ \\n    15│ ## Three-Tool Synergy\\n    16│ \\n    17│ ### 1. features.json (Static Configuration)\\n    18│ \\n    19│ **Role**: Source of truth for project scope, acceptance criteria, and dependency graph.\\n    20│ \\n    21│ **Content**:\\n    22│ - Feature definitions (id, title, description)\\n    23│ - Acceptance criteria (type: command/test/assertion/manual)\\n    24│ - Dependency graph (which features block which)\\n    25│ - Wave assignments (planning hints, not enforced)\\n    26│ - Estimated complexity and token budgets\\n    27│ - Owner agent assignments\\n    28│ \\n    29│ **Lifecycle**:\\n    30│ - Created during PRD Phase 2 (Decomposition)\\n    31│ - Updated when scope changes (new features, modified acceptance criteria)\\n    32│ - Imported into DB at project initialization\\n    33│ - Exported from DB for backup/archival\\n    34│ \\n    35│ **Schema Version**: 2 (added fields: schema_version, generated_by, generation_date, notes)\\n    36│ \\n    37│ ### 2. pipeline_state.db (Dynamic State)\\n    38│ \\n    39│ **Role**: Runtime record of all development activities, costs, and outcomes.\\n    40│ \\n    41│ **Tables**:\\n    42│ \\n    43│ #### projects\\n    44│ ```sql\\n    45│ id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n    46│ name TEXT NOT NULL,\\n    47│ current_phase TEXT NOT NULL,\\n    48│ schema_version INTEGER DEFAULT 2,\\n    49│ base_dir TEXT,           -- project root path\\n    50│ features_json_path TEXT, -- path to features.json\\n    51│ github_repo TEXT,        -- GitHub repo URL\\n    52│ created_at TIMESTAMP,\\n    53│ updated_at TIMESTAMP\\n    54│ ```\\n    55│ \\n    56│ #### features (enhanced)\\n    57│ ```sql\\n    58│ id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n    59│ project_id TEXT REFERENCES projects(id),\\n    60│ title TEXT NOT NULL,\\n    61│ description TEXT,\\n    62│ status TEXT CHECK(status IN ('pending','in_progress','completed','reviewed','tested','passed','failed','skipped')),\\n    63│ owner_agent TEXT,\\n    64│ estimated_complexity TEXT,\\n    65│ wave INTEGER,\\n    66│ max_token_budget INTEGER,\\n    67│ token_cost INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\\n    68│ dependencies TEXT,       -- JSON array of feature IDs\\n    69│ acceptance_criteria TEXT, -- JSON array of criteria objects\\n    70│ created_at TIMESTAMP,\\n    71│ updated_at TIMESTAMP\\n    72│ ```\\n    73│ \\n    74│ #### checkpoints (unchanged)\\n    75│ ```sql\\n    76│ id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\\n    77│ project_id TEXT REFERENCES projects(id),\\n    78│ phase TEXT NOT NULL,\\n    79│ feature_id TEXT,\\n    80│ agent TEXT,\\n    81│ action TEXT,\\n    82│ result TEXT,\\n    83│ state_json TEXT NOT NULL,\\n    84│ created_at TIMESTAMP\\n    85│ ```\\n    86│ \\n    87│ #### traces (unchanged)\\n    88│ ```sql\\n    89│ id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\\n    90│ project_id TEXT,\\n    91│ feature_id TEXT,\\n    92│ agent TEXT,\\n    93│ model TEXT,\\n    94│ input_tokens INTEGER,\\n    95│ output_tokens INTEGER,\\n    96│ cost_usd REAL,\\n    97│ latency_ms INTEGER,\\n    98│ status TEXT,\\n    99│ cache_hit BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,\\n   100│ created_at TIMESTAMP\\n\\n[TRUNCATED] Showing lines 1-100 of 539. To continue, call read_file with path=\\\"C:\\\\tmp\\\\multi-agent-pipeline\\\\docs\\\\architecture_v2.md\\\" start_line=101 max_lines=100\\n</file>\"",
